BEGIN_PGML
For a falling object on Mars, with height measured in feet and time measured in seconds, the curvature coefficient of its height function is (roughly) [`-6\text{.}`]

An object on Mars is shot straight up from a height of [`[$c]`] feet with an initial speed of [`[$c]`] feet per second. How long will it take for the object to land?

[_]{$answer}{16}

END_PGML

